Installing from source
======================

Debian systems
--------------
copy the "marchobmenu/usr/lib/marchobmenu" directory to your "/usr/lib directory"
$ sudo cp -R marchobmenu/usr/lib/marchobmenu /usr/lib

copy the "marchobmenu/etc/init.d/marchobmenu" file to your "/etc/init.d directory"
$ sudo cp marchobmenu/etc/init.d/marchobmenu /etc/init.d

symlink "marchobmenu/etc/init.d/marchobmenu" to /etc/rcS.d/S56marchobmenu
$ sudo ln -s /etc/init.d/marchobmenu /etc/rcS.d/S56marchobmenu

start the daemon
$ sudo /etc/init.d/marchobmenu start

add the following line to your ~/.config/openbox/autostart.sh file
/usr/lib/marchobmenu/./marchobmenu-launcher &> /dev/null

add the following line to your ~/.config/openbox/menu.xml file
<menu label="Applications" id="marchobmenu-applications" execute="/usr/lib/marchobmenu/applications" />

You can also add the places menu.
Replace "~" by any directory you want as a starting point, and "thunar" by the file manager of your choice.
<menu label="Places" id="marchobmenu-places" execute="/usr/lib/marchobmenu/places ~ thunar"/>


Installing from a package
===========================

Debian package
--------------

The root daemon should start right after installing the package. If it doesn't, you can start it manually with:
$ sudo /etc/init.d/marchobmenu start

After that, it will just start automatically at boot.

You will have to launch the user daemon in your Openbox startup file (~/.config/openbox/autostart.sh).
Simply add the following line at an appropriate place.

/usr/lib/marchobmenu/./marchobmenu-launcher &> /dev/null


The "Applications" menu is built by parsing the .desktop entries in /usr/share/applications
to an xml file located in ~/.config/openbox/marchobmenu/applications.xml

You can add it to your Openbox menu like this:
<menu label="Applications" id="marchobmenu-applications" execute="/usr/lib/marchobmenu/applications" />


There is also a "Places" menu available that will allow you to browse your filesystem
from your Openbox menu.
<menu label="Places" id="marchobmenu-places" execute="/usr/lib/marchobmenu/places ~ thunar" />

You can replace "~" by any directory you want as a starting point,
and "thunar" by the file manager of your choice.